content: over most of the planet, conifers are everywhere except the salt flats around the salt lakes, the scrub around that, and the wetlands around the brackish deltas that give way to that scrub and flats. conifers are from the snow lines to the ravine floors. in the middle altitudes down, there are ample hardwoods with nuts, seeds, and fruit, while in the lower part of the middle, palm-like trees appear and become very numerous in the lowest altitudes closest to the salt lakes
